msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:14
msgid ""
"While not a part of the chapters for an LXD Server, this procedure will help "
"those who wish to have a lab environment, or semi-permanent OS and "
"application, running on a Rocky Linux workstation or laptop."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:22
msgid "comfortable at the command line"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:22
msgid "able to use a command line editor, such as `vi` or `nano` fluently"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:22
msgid "willing to install `snapd` in order to install LXD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:22
msgid ""
"a desire for a stable testing environment that can be used every day or as "
"needed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:22
msgid "able to become root or have `sudo` privileges"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:26
msgid "From the command line, install the EPEL repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf install epel-release \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:32
msgid "Once installed, do an upgrade:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf upgrade\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:38
msgid "Install `snapd`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo dnf install snapd \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:44
msgid "Enable the `snapd` service"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo systemctl enable snapd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:50
msgid "Reboot your laptop or workstation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:52
msgid "Install the snap for LXD:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo snap install lxd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "LXD Initialization"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:60
msgid ""
"If you've looked through the production server chapters, this is very "
"similiar to the production server init procedure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo lxd init\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:66
msgid ""
"This will bring up a question and answer dialog that looks like the "
"following."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:68
msgid ""
"Here are the questions and our answers for the script, with a little "
"explanation where warranted:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "Would you like to use LXD clustering? (yes/no) [default=no]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:74
msgid ""
"If you are interested in clustering, do some additional research on that "
"[here](https://linuxcontainers.org/lxd/docs/master/clustering/)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:75
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Do you want to configure a new storage pool? (yes/no) [default=yes]:\n"
"Name of the new storage pool [default=default]: storage\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:81
msgid ""
"Optionally, you can accept the default. Since we aren't using ZFS, it really "
"is just a choice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Name of the storage backend to use (btrfs, dir, lvm, ceph) [default=btrfs]: dir\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Note that dir is somewhat slower than btrfs. If you have the forsight to leave a disk empty, you can use that device (example: /dev/sdb)\n"
" as the btrfs device and then choose btrfs. dir will work fine\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "Would you like to connect to a MAAS server? (yes/no) [default=no]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:94
msgid "Metal As A Service (MAAS) is outside the scope of this document."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:95
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Would you like to create a new local network bridge? (yes/no) [default=yes]:\n"
"What should the new bridge be called? [default=lxdbr0]: \n"
"What IPv4 address should be used? (CIDR subnet notation, âautoâ or ânoneâ) [default=auto]:\n"
"What IPv6 address should be used? (CIDR subnet notation, âautoâ or ânoneâ) [default=auto]: none\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:103
msgid ""
"If you want to use IPv6 on your LXD containers, you can turn on this option. "
"That is up to you."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "Would you like the LXD server to be available over the network? (yes/no) [default=no]: yes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:109
msgid "This is necessary to snapshot the server, so answer \"yes\" here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:110
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Address to bind LXD to (not including port) [default=all]:\n"
"Port to bind LXD to [default=8443]:\n"
"Trust password for new clients:\n"
"Again:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:119
msgid ""
"This trust password is how you will connect to the snapshot server or back "
"from the snapshot server, so set this with something that mak es sense in "
"your environment. Save this entry to a secure location, such as a password "
"manager."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Would you like stale cached images to be updated automatically? (yes/no) [default=yes]\n"
"Would you like a YAML \"lxd init\" preseed to be printed? (yes/no) [default=no]:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "User Privileges"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:128
msgid ""
"The next thing you need to do is to add your user to the lxd group. Again, "
"you will need to use `sudo` or be root for this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "sudo usermod -a -G lxd [username]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:134
msgid "where [username] is your user on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:136
msgid ""
"At this point, you've made a bunch of changes so before you go any further, "
"reboot your machne."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying the Install"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:140
msgid ""
"To make sure that `lxd` started and that your user has privileges, from the "
"command prompt do:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc list\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:146
msgid ""
"Note we have not used `sudo` here as your user should now have the ability "
"to enter these commands.  You should get something like this in return:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"+------------+---------+----------------------+------+-----------+-----------+\n"
"|    NAME    |  STATE  |         IPV4         | IPV6 |   TYPE    | SNAPSHOTS |\n"
"+------------+---------+----------------------+------+-----------+-----------+\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/30-appendix_a.md:154
msgid "If so, you're looking good so far!"
msgstr ""

